sentences: Birger Wøllner Gaarn   (3 August 1881 – 10 August 1949) was a Danish organist, organ teacher and composer.
He graduated from the Royal Danish Academy of Music in 1902, and was the organist at Christian's Church, Copenhagen from 1907 to 1949.
